oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Perry Paulsen Simms house in Cherry Creek
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Perry Paulsen Simms house in Cherry Creek. There are many people on the porch.
Built by his mother, Lucinda Mae Glenn Sims, around 1859. The name Simms has various spellings within the family.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Dwellings; Houses; Porches; Fences; People
